SIMPLE: saddle-shaped
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saddle-shaped
<hw>Sad"dle-shaped`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Shaped like a
saddle.</def> Specifically: <sd>(a)</sd> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Bent
down at the sides so as to give the upper part a rounded form.</def>
<rj><au>Henslow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sd>(b)</sd> <fld>(Geol.)</fld> <def>Bent on each side of a mountain
or ridge, without being broken at top; -- said of strata.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Saddletree</ent>⟦br⟧
